Description: Tools for computing geospatial and infrastructural measures of
    urbanicity using OpenStreetMap and Google Earth Engine. Supports multi-year
    analysis of population density (WorldPop), nighttime light intensity (VIIRS),
    and settlement classification (GHSL Degree of Urbanisation) to track
    urbanization trends over time. Includes travel-time measures to key
    facilities and urban centers. Raster data are accessed on demand through
    Earth Engine via 'rgee'. Developed for the Population Ecology, Aging, and
    Health Network (PEcAHN).
